Over the entire period considered here, the spread was positive, meaning that southern state bonds were riskier on average than northern state bonds.
\footnote{That southern bonds have a higher risk premium during this period is somewhat surprising givne the northern bonds; two of the three northern state bonds (Indiana, Pennsylvania) had defaulted in the 1840s.}

